    "body": "We've been hitting this exact issue in production (OpenClaw 2026.2.6, Linux arm64, AWS ECS). Cron scheduler silently dies during deploys ‚Äî all jobs stop firing with no log output. Gateway otherwise healthy.\n\nOur current workaround is a cloud-init patch that restarts the gateway after initial boot to kick the scheduler back to life. Would love to remove that once this lands.\n\nThe root cause analysis matches what we observed: 20+ hour gaps with no cron activity despite the gateway responding normally to API calls. üëç",
