    "body": "## Rebase update (Feb 8)\n\nRebased onto latest `main` to resolve the merge conflict in `src/cron/service/timer.ts`.\n\n### What changed in the conflict resolution\n\nThe conflict was in `armTimer()` at the `if (!nextAt)` branch. Upstream added diagnostic debug logging (jobCount, enabledCount, withNextRun) in the same location where this PR adds the `!state.store` retry logic.\n\n**Resolution:** combined both changes with an `if/else`:\n\n- `if (!state.store)` ‚Üí this PR's retry logic (schedule a 60s retry timer so the scheduler recovers from transient I/O failures)\n- `else` ‚Üí upstream's debug logging (log job counts when no jobs have a nextRunAtMs)\n\nNo logic changes beyond the conflict merge. The three fixes (start() resilience, store retry, catch re-arm) remain as described in the original PR.\n",
